HEADWORD: Ecce homo
<hw>Ec"ce ho"mo</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧k"s⟦esl⟧ h⟦omac⟧"m⟦osl⟧)</pr>.
<ety>[L., behold the man. See John xix. 5.]</ety> <fld>(Paint.)</fld>
<def>A picture which represents the Savior as given up to the people by
Pilate, and wearing a crown of thorns.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eccentric</ent>⟦br⟧
